@JockoShard @Mr_Jobling_ Fun fact- 
the E2s share the same boiler and cylinders as the I2 variant, however the E2s were adequate steamers because the source of the steaming trouble on the I1/2/4s was the firebox being too far from the boiler to generate enough heat.
full_text(utf-8): b'@JockoShard @Mr_Jobling_ Fun fact- \nthe E2s share the same boiler and cylinders as the I2 variant, however the E2s were adequate steamers because the source of the steaming trouble on the I1/2/4s was the firebox being too far from the boiler to generate enough heat.'

b'@JockoShard @Mr_Jobling_ These things were far more pathetic than the E2s ever were-

The I1s failed at the same type of work: passenger trains in the suburbs of London. 
They attempted to correct them with the I2 and I4 iterations of the class, and STILL fucked it up.'

b'@JockoShard @Mr_Jobling_ Yeah, I'd say the same for any 0-6-0 shunter

The E2s are judged based on mostly minor short-comings, in reality they were merely average

Now, if you want a REAL failure from Brighton Works, look at the I1/2/4 class, which earned the name "Wankers" from how badly they steamed https://t.co/rBqGVlMMdR'

full_text:
@Mr_Jobling_ Yes, a 57xx would also pitch and roll if it went fast enough, but usually 0-6-0s don't need to go particularly fast.
The E2 was out of it's element pulling those commuter trains, so its no wonder it didn't work.
full_text(utf-8): b"@Mr_Jobling_ Yes, a 57xx would also pitch and roll if it went fast enough, but usually 0-6-0s don't need to go particularly fast.\nThe E2 was out of it's element pulling those commuter trains, so its no wonder it didn't work."

full_text:
@Mr_Jobling_ Oscillation at higher speeds is a problem that comes with any steam loco wheel arrangement that doesn't have any leading or trailing wheels, they're less stable when going fast.

This is why passenger engines such as the Lanky tanks, for example, have them. https://t.co/HfL7OLP7jA
full_text(utf-8): b"@Mr_Jobling_ Oscillation at higher speeds is a problem that comes with any steam loco wheel arrangement that doesn't have any leading or trailing wheels, they're less stable when going fast.\n\nThis is why passenger engines such as the Lanky tanks, for example, have them. https://t.co/HfL7OLP7jA"

full_text: So if you ever have to experience something as hellish as having an inflamed appendix and have it removed surgically, don't jump right back into school/work just because you feel obligated. Give yourself the time you need to recover both physically AND mentally.
full_text(utf-8): b"So if you ever have to experience something as hellish as having an inflamed appendix and have it removed surgically, don't jump right back into school/work just because you feel obligated. Give yourself the time you need to recover both physically AND mentally."

full_text: The whole reason I tried to rush back into resuming online classes is because I thought that was way more important than giving myself plenty of time to recover from what one might consider a traumatic event.
full_text(utf-8): b'The whole reason I tried to rush back into resuming online classes is because I thought that was way more important than giving myself plenty of time to recover from what one might consider a traumatic event.'

full_text:
Not so much by college in my case, but in the years leading up to it I was taught that school itself is your greatest priority. 
Even if it was likely triggered by surgery itself, it took losing days of sleep to realize what a shit mentality that is to enstill in a person
full_text(utf-8): b'Not so much by college in my case, but in the years leading up to it I was taught that school itself is your greatest priority. \nEven if it was likely triggered by surgery itself, it took losing days of sleep to realize what a shit mentality that is to enstill in a person'

full_text: Lastly, and arguably the most important thing I realized in my experience over the last couple weeks is how much sacraficing self-care has been normalized in today's society and how absolutely fucking dangerous that is https://t.co/H2XbHwplsg
